        "created_at": "2025-07-13T17:06:00.475Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi all,</p>\n<p>I have a Samsung smartphone and smartwatch. Signal is installed on the phone. When I receive a message and the phone is connected to the smartwatch via bluetooth I receive the notification on the watch an can answer.</p>\n<p>Up to now, this is all easy to understand.</p>\n<p>But since a few days I have a SIM card in my smartwatch so that the watch can connect to the internet and mobile phone network independent from the smartphone. Today, when I was on the road without my smartphone I received signal messages on the watch and could even reply. When I arrived back home I checked the smartphone and all messages where on the phone too.</p>\n<p>How does this works? Especially since there is no dedicated signal app for Android wearable.</p>",
