        "created_at": "2025-07-13T17:13:39.745Z",
        "cooked": "<p>There‚Äôs a common misconception that you can‚Äôt receive notifications on an Android smartwatch if there is no companion smartwatch app for a given phone app. I can‚Äôt speak to iPhones and Apple Watches, but on Android, there is a sort of ‚Äúhalfway-function‚Äù that exists, which is just ‚Äúnotification mirroring‚Äù.</p>\n<p>If the phone and the watch are connected to the Internet, Signal is not at all dependent on the phone SIM for the mobile number after registration, so it‚Äôs as simple as sending notifications from the phone over the Internet to the watch, and you can respond from the watch whether there‚Äôs a standalone app or not.</p>\n<p>With Signal specifically, what you can‚Äôt do without a standalone smartwatch app is start new conversations or view an existing conversation without having first received a notification.</p>",
